{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.34",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 34,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 34",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 34 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:1",
      "text": "Moreover Elihu answered,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:2",
      "text": "“ Hear my words, you wise men. Give ear to me, you who have knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:3",
      "text": "For the ear tries words, as the palate tastes food.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:4",
      "text": "Let us choose for us that which is right. Let us know among ourselves what is good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:5",
      "text": "For Job has said, ‘ I am righteous, God has taken away my right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:6",
      "text": "Notwithstanding my right I am considered a liar. My wound is incurable, though I am without disobedience.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:7",
      "text": "What man is like Job, who drinks scorn like water,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:8",
      "text": "who goes in company with the workers of iniquity, and walks with wicked men?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:9",
      "text": "For he has said, ‘ It profits a man nothing that he should delight himself with God.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:10",
      "text": "“ Therefore listen to me, you men of understanding: far be it from God, that he should do wickedness, from the Almighty, that he should commit iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:11",
      "text": "For the work of a man he will give to him, and cause every man to find according to his ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:12",
      "text": "Yes surely, God will not do wickedly, neither will the Almighty pervert justice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:13",
      "text": "Who put him in charge of the earth? Or who has appointed him over the whole world?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:14",
      "text": "If he set his heart on himself, if he gathered to himself his spirit and his breath,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:15",
      "text": "all flesh would perish together, and man would turn again to dust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:16",
      "text": "“If now you have understanding, hear this. Listen to the voice of my words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:17",
      "text": "Should even one who hates justice govern? Will you condemn him who is righteous and mighty,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:18",
      "text": "who says to a king, ‘Vile!’ or to nobles, ‘ Wicked!’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:19",
      "text": "He doesn’t respect the persons of princes, nor respect the rich more than the poor, for they all are the work of his hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:20",
      "text": "In a moment they die, even at midnight. The people are shaken and pass away. The mighty are taken away without a hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:21",
      "text": "“ For his eyes are on the ways of a man. He sees all his goings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:22",
      "text": "There is no darkness, nor thick gloom, where the workers of iniquity may hide themselves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:23",
      "text": "For he doesn’t need to consider a man further, that he should go before God in judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:24",
      "text": "He breaks mighty men in pieces in ways past finding out, and sets others in their place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:25",
      "text": "Therefore he takes knowledge of their works. He overturns them in the night, so that they are destroyed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:26",
      "text": "He strikes them as wicked men in the open sight of others;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:27",
      "text": "because they turned away from following him, and wouldn’t pay attention to any of his ways,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:28",
      "text": "so that they caused the cry of the poor to come to him. He heard the cry of the afflicted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:29",
      "text": "When he gives quietness, who then can condemn? When he hides his face, who then can see him? He is over a nation or a man alike,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:30",
      "text": "that the godless man may not reign, that there be no one to ensnare the people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:31",
      "text": "“ For has any said to God, ‘ I am guilty, but I will not offend any more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:32",
      "text": "Teach me that which I don’t see. If I have done iniquity, I will do it no more ’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:33",
      "text": "Shall his recompense be as you desire, that you refuse it? For you must choose, and not I. Therefore speak what you know.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:34",
      "text": "Men of understanding will tell me, yes, every wise man who hears me:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:35",
      "text": "‘ Job speaks without knowledge. His words are without wisdom.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.36",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:36",
      "text": "I wish that Job were tried to the end, because of his answering like wicked men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.34.37",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:37",
      "text": "For he adds rebellion to his sin. He claps his hands among us, and multiplies his words against God.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
